  "prompt": "I feel a strong connection with someone but I don't know if they feel they same way back, how can I ask them?",
  "response": "Here are some suggestions for approaching this delicate situation:\n\n1. Start with casual conversation and spend more time together to gauge their interest\n\n2. Look for signs they might like you back:\n- They make time for you\n- They seem happy when you're around\n- They text/call frequently\n- Their body language seems positive\n\n3. When you're ready to express your feelings, consider:\n- Being direct but gentle\n- Choosing a comfortable, private setting\n- Using \"I\" statements like \"I really enjoy spending time with you\"\n- Being prepared for any response\n\n4. If you're nervous, you could:\n- Write a letter\n- Tell a trusted friend first for support\n- Practice what you want to say\n\n5. Possible conversation starters:\n- \"I feel a special connection with you\"\n- \"I really care about you and wanted to be honest about my feelings\"\n- \"I'm wondering if you might feel the same way about me\"\n\n6. Be prepared to:\n- Respect their feelings\n- Accept their response graciously\n- Maintain the friendship if they don't feel the same\n\nRemember, courage and honesty are key. Good luck!\n\nWould you like to discuss this more specifically?",
